I have made this for years and it is always amazing. Try making it with finely ground corn meal which will yield a creamy very smooth polenta. Also vary the cheeses and/or add fresh corn. I often omit the ham and serve it with a vegetable ragu of tomatoes and seasonal vegetables. Without the ham it is a wonderful vegetarian entre.

Rating: 4
I really like the basic idea here and that's what I'm giving 4-forks. I modified it as follows. I doubled the recipe to ensure leftovers. For liquid, I used 1/2 milk and 1/2 water. I used 1/2 the butter called and parmesan. I trimmed and quartered a pound of regular white mushrooms and sauteed them in 3 T. of butter. When the shrooms were almost done, I added 3 cloves of chopped garlic. and let it get translucent. I added the mushroom/garlic mix when I added the ham. Make sure you use unsalted butter. The parmesan and ham contain plenty of salt. If you don't like salty food, don't add any extra salt.

Rating: 4
I love this recipe. It has everything I'm looking for in a one-dish meal: carbohydrates, protein and fat, not to mention deliciousness. I sometimes vary the meat and use bacon or a good quality sausage, and sometimes I use another cheese like a sharp cheddar. And then again there are those days that I put some sauteed and cooled vegetables in too: onion, zucchini, cooked and squeezed chopped spinach or even sun dried tomatoes. That way I get everything I need for one meal, all in one delicious dish. I always double the recipe and cut some up into wedges and freeze them. I've also reduced the butter to about half, and substituted half the milk with chicken stock, to no adverse reactions at all. I'm going to make some right now!

